<br>
We will be operating on the now (hopefully) familair Triage-Healing tactic.  All classes capable of binding in the pre-lair &quot;ready room&quot; MUST BIND there (we'll make it clear during the raid as to exactly where this is).  If you don't bind, you don't roll on loot.  Pretty simple.<br>
<br>
The Triage area where healers set up will be at the corner of the stairs facing into the lair (slightly closer than it has been previously).  Again, we'll make it very clear where this is when we get there.<br>
<br>
There will one or two waves of tanks (depending on classes and levels present).  Tanks will try and fight Nagefen in the MIDDLE of his room, NOT at the very back - we want to keep him out of range of the triage area without making the run back to get healed too extended.  Keeping pressure on the beast is the best way to ensure it's death.  All tanks that have resistant discipline should use it as soon as Nagefen is engaged.  It lasts for 5 minutes, helps ward off both the AoE Fear and AoE Lava spells.  If we can't kill Naggy in 5 minutes, we've probably lost...<br>
<br>
After the first AoE Fear goes off, all pets will be sent in.  Mages should use fire pets for preference, as they will resist Nagefen's AoE fire spells and hopefully live long enough to do some decent melee damage.<br>
<br>
When Nagefen is at or around 50% life casters will go in and nuke for all they're worth.  The exact timing on when casters will be called in depends on how the tanks are doing... if tanks start dying off sooner than expected, casters will need to go in sooner.<br>
<br>
The basic idea here is that the tanks go in and generate as much taunt as possible to allow the casters time to get in and do as much damage as possible - and of course the healers try to keep the tanks alive as long as possible.<br>
<br>
Minimum un-buffed resistances should be 70 for both Magic and Fire resistance.  Healer classes can go lower than this in order to keep their wisdom up for mana, but should still try to remain above 50.  Healers especially need to make sure they have enough Magic resistance to keep from being feared constantly.<br>
<br>
If you do not meet these resistance requirements - do whatever you can to get your MR and FR as high as possible.  Tanks especially need high resistances in order to live long enough to contribute to a successful raid.  If you have sub-standard resistances, you will suck away more healer mana than other tanks (who are fighting longer than you), and in the process of running back for heals you will be fighting the dragon for less time, doing less damage.<br>
<br>
<br>
Nagafen and Fire Giant loot rules:<br>
<br>
Almost all items are to be rolled on by any class that can use them.  There are, however, some exceptions - I've tried to list them all here.  If I've forgotten something, we'll deal with it when it comes... but all decisions made by raid admin are final.<br>
<br>
Cloak of Flames:  This item is to be rolled on by MELEE classes only.  Quite frankly a caster or priest has no where near the need for haste that a melee class does, and it will make us all stronger if items are used by those that will use them best.<br>
<br>
Polished Mithril Torque:  This item is to be rolled on by HYBRIDS only (Paladin, Ranger, Shadowknight).  There is better AC to be had for the other melee classes (even Fine Plate has better AC), and the +13 Wisdom and Int will be better used by a hybrid class.<br>
<br>
Rokyl's Channeling Crystal: This item is to be rolled on by PURE CASTERS only (Wizard, Necromancer, Enchanter, Magician).  Bards can use it, but, frankly, probably wouldn't even if they had it.<br>
<br>
*EDIT*<br>
Polished Mithril Mask: This item is to be rolled on by PRIEST and CASTER classes only.  They can make better use of the Wis/Int bonus, and Tanks can get the same AC out of store-bought steel or even bronze if they want it.<br>
*EDIT*<br>
<br>
Whenever possible we will try to pre-roll on NO DROP items that may drop in upcoming encounters.  This will allow faster ressurection should the winner die during the conflict, and will avoid wasting time trying to get everyone elligable to roll res'd before rolls begin.<br>
<br>
That's it everyone - I hope to see as many of you as possible in the near future, and would like nothing more than tip back a few ale's in good company while looking at the body of a dead Red Dragon! <p>-Kommisar Nils "Can-Head" Hansen -- Guild Officer. Master Smith. Tank.
